SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 878
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor Diana Fisher, 2026 recipient of the John
J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Diana Fisher, who was recently named the 2026
recipient of the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy; and
WHEREAS, the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy was created to honor
those who steadfastly work to improve the lives of seniors in the Knoxville community, as the
award's namesake did throughout his career; recipients are professionals and community
members who have been nominated in recognition of their tireless efforts on behalf of seniors;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Fisher began her professional journey as an activities assistant in a
nursing home, working directly with residents and discovering what would become her life's
calling: caring for seniors with dignity, compassion, and excellence; and
WHEREAS, after earning a bachelor's degree in social work from East Tennessee State
University, she served as a medical social worker, supporting patients and families through
some of life's most challenging transitions and shaping a leadership philosophy grounded in the
principle that operational excellence must always serve people first; and
WHEREAS, Diana Fisher steadily advanced through roles in admissions, regional
marketing, and facility administration, successfully leading both seventy-nine-bed and 182-bed
skilled nursing facilities; she built strong teams, strengthened census performance, and
maintained regulatory integrity while balancing accountability with compassion; and
SJR0878
014126
- 1 -

WHEREAS, today, as Senior Vice President of Strategy and Business Operations for
Hillcrest Healthcare, Ms. Fisher leads system-wide growth initiatives, operational performance
strategies, and program expansion across post-acute services; her leadership has strengthened
financial stability, enhanced quality outcomes, and positioned her organization for long-term
success; and
WHEREAS, Diana Fisher's influence extends beyond her organization, as she has
served on the Statewide Coordinated Community Response Team as the Knoxville Regional
Representative and currently serves on the Board of Directors for the Tennessee Center for
Performance Excellence and on the Institutional Review Board for the University of Tennessee
Medical Center, advancing quality, ethics, and accountability in health care statewide; and
WHEREAS, no stranger to accolades, she is the recipient of the Columbia/HCA
Caregiving Award, a testament to her lifelong commitment to compassionate leadership; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her professional endeavors, Diana Fisher serves on the
worship team at Piney Grove Baptist Church and is most proud of being a devoted wife to Dave
and mother to Zack; and
WHEREAS, for more than four decades, Ms. Fisher has exemplified selfless leadership
through her unwavering commitment to older adults and their families; her career is a powerful
reminder that leadership is not defined by position but by service, integrity, and the lives one
impacts along the way; and
WHEREAS, Diana Fisher is most worthy of our approbation on this special occasion;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Diana Fisher, 2026
- 2 - 014126

recipient of the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy, extending our best wishes for
her continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
